<br>
If the pet becomes a mage we´ll one problem:<br>
<br>
° Zones like <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Tower of Solusek Ro</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Plane of Fire</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> where Fire Damage will severely reduce the pet´s usefullness as mob are simply immune.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mage DD Spells &lt; lvl 52 </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (Fire: Char, Lava Bolt // Magic: Shock of Swords)<br>
<br>
To make the pet worthwhile casting in the 2 zones i mentioned above (talking about the lvl 63 pet atm), SOE would need to make sure it casts Shock of Swords only. If Recast Time applies to pets it could theoretically do ~ 72 dps max in those zones - assuming there is no resist at all. As Mages have access to Mala and Malosinia i would say this is the easiest solution to everyone´s problem.<br>
<br>
Sadly though Jabober also has access to Fire Based Spells if they don´t limit it´s spells. This means the max dps will go down - WAY down.<br>
<br>
Now how to solve this dilemma?<br>
<br>
° Remove recast time for pets? No, would overpower it in other zones<br>
° Add special pet dd spells to its aresenal? Probably, but then it would mean more work and knowing SOE that just won´t happen <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
° Reduce the pet´s spell access to one spell type only: Magic (can´t think of any zone where this will be resisted atm) - Best solution imo, but also requires some work.<br>
<br>
Option 3 however requires the pet to have unlimited mana to be able to contribute to exp groups - Considering it is doing 72 dps max only, i guess this is a compromise mages 'could' live with.<br>
<br>
Stopping the Pet from meleeing would be simple. Just use the code for Servant of Ro (Mage AA skill: Summons a mini pet, rooted and casts only one type of spell - 150dd fire based lure). A spell range of 200 would ensure the pet is able damage mobs even a far away from camp.<br>
<br>
What do you think? <br>
